<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ870518-0068 </DOCNO><HL> Sun Microsystems Inc.</HL><DD> 05/18/87</DD><SO> WALL STREET JOURNAL (J)</SO><IN> SUNW CCI </IN><DATELINE> MOUNTAIN VIEW, Calif.  </DATELINE><TEXT>   Sun Microsystems Inc. said it will provide Citicorp's Quotron Systems Inc. unit with technical workstations to be sold in conjunction with Quotron's own computerized stock information systems.    Quotron will offer the workstations as an optional terminal for its Global Trading System, which displays, analyzes and updates market information. The Sun workstations, which more commonly are used by engineers and professional printers, will be able simultaneously to display Quotron information and execute trades. </TEXT></DOC>